input: Objective: Go to Google Docs and start a new document
output:
I'm sorry for any confusion, but I'm an AI model running on a platform that doesn't allow direct interactions with external websites like Google Docs. However, I can guide you on how to create a new document there.

Here are the steps:

1. Open your web browser and go to [Google Drive](https://drive.google.com/).
2. Click on the "+ New" icon at the top left corner.
3. Select "Google Docs".
4. A new blank document will open, titled "Untitled document". You can now start typing your content there.
5. To save your document, click on "File" in the menu bar, then select "Save", or use the keyboard shortcut `Ctrl + S` (Windows/Linux) or `Cmd + S` (Mac).
